1. Definitions
“Project” means the work in this repository, including source code and associated files.
“Excerpt” means a limited portion of the Project’s source code.
“Substantial” means more than the Excerpt limits in Section 3.

2. Permission
You may view, study, and use the ideas and techniques from the Project for any purpose. You may copy and adapt Excerpts for any purpose, subject to Attribution and Limits below.

3. Excerpt Limits
You may copy at most the lesser of:
  (a) 200 contiguous lines from any single file; and
  (b) 10% of the lines of that file; and
  (c) 10% of the total lines of source code in the Project.
All three caps apply. Aggregating multiple Excerpts to recreate a substantial part of the Project is not allowed.

4. Attribution
If you use any Excerpt, you must give reasonable attribution:
  • Include a NOTICE naming the Project, OWNER, the repository URL, and this license.
  • Mark changes you made to any Excerpt.
  • Do not suggest endorsement by OWNER.

